# Walkthrough: Nginx Server Name Configuration

I have updated the Nginx configuration to properly identify the Frontend VM by both its IP address and its default network name.

## Work Accomplished

### 1. Hostname Discovery
Since SSH access was unavailable via automated means, I used the **NetBIOS** lookup tool (`nbtstat`) to identify the default network name of the VM.
- **Frontend VM (`10.172.19.16`)**: Discovered as **`ADCERPWEB`**.
- **Backend VM (`10.172.19.15`)**: Discovered as **`ADCERPAPI`**.

### 2. Configuration Updates
I updated the following files to include `ADCERPWEB` alongside the IP address in the `server_name` directive:

#### [nginx.conf](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/nginx.conf)
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name 10.172.19.16 ADCERPWEB;
    ...
}
```

#### [nginx-windows.conf](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/nginx-windows.conf)
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name 10.172.19.16 ADCERPWEB;
    ...
}
```

## Verification Results

### Automated Tests
I verified the changes using `grep` to ensure both entries were present in both configuration files:

```bash
grep -r "server_name" .
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Output:**
> - `nginx.conf:10`: `server_name 10.172.19.16 ADCERPWEB;`
> - `nginx-windows.conf:11`: `server_name 10.172.19.16 ADCERPWEB;`

## Next Steps

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To apply these changes to the live production server, you must run the deployment script:
> ```powershell
> .\deploy-v2.ps1
> ```
> This script will push the updated `nginx-windows.conf` to the VM and restart the Nginx service.
